1
00:00:17,726 --> 00:00:23,481
{\an8}-I have no idea what you're tryin' to say.
-I mean, I can't help it.

2
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:27,402
Furin's Four Kings
are all right in front of my eyes!

3
00:00:28,236 --> 00:00:29,487
Who's what again?

4
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:31,656
Huh? Don't call them "what"!

5
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:32,907
Okay...

6
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:33,867
{\an8}CONFIDENTIAL

7
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:37,662
The head of the Jikoku Team,
Tsubakino-san.

8
00:00:38,288 --> 00:00:41,041
The head of the Komoku Team, Mizuki-san.

9
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:44,419
The head of the Zojo Team, Momose-san.

10
00:00:45,044 --> 00:00:48,256
{\an8}And the head of our Tamon Team,
Hiragi-san.

11
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:51,676
{\an8}They're the core members of Bofurin.

12
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:54,763
Thanks for gathering here, guys!

13
00:00:54,846 --> 00:01:00,226
So all of you here
are gonna be leading Bofurin.

14
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:04,689
{\an8}But before we begin,
I need you guys to know.

15
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:08,151
{\an8}I'm sure some of you've noticed...

16
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:13,114
{\an8}but I've successfully transplanted
the seedlings for this year!

17
00:01:13,198 --> 00:01:14,032
Huh?

18
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:15,366
SMUG

19
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:18,578
Sugishita over there
has been helping me out a ton!

20
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:22,415
We've planted a lot this year,
so we'll be having a feast!

21
00:01:22,499 --> 00:01:25,627
Look forward to an amazing
barbecue party this summer!

22
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:29,047
Umemiya, do you have to
bring that up at this time?

23
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:32,884
But I finally finished planting,
so I wanted everyone to see!

24
00:01:32,967 --> 00:01:36,888
At least greet all the grade captains
who are lining up for you.

25
00:01:36,971 --> 00:01:39,098
{\an8}Greetings...

26
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:42,185
{\an8}I didn't plan to do something
so grandiose, though...

27
00:01:43,019 --> 00:01:45,438
{\an8}But, well, I guess I can do one thing.

28
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:46,689
{\an8}You guys.

29
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:49,442
{\an8}I'm counting on you.

30
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:53,738
{\an8}There is little I can do alone.

31
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:58,618
{\an8}Much less keeping an eye
on everyone in this school.

32
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,663
So I'd like to ask all of you to help.

33
00:02:02,247 --> 00:02:06,668
I want you guys to watch and help
all of our friends here and there.

34
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:10,380
I'm counting on you guys.

35
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,173
Yes, sir!

36
00:02:20,723 --> 00:02:24,853
So, for now, gather up with the guys in
your team and get to know each other.

37
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:29,566
So you became the grade captain
of our first year, yeah?

38
00:02:30,024 --> 00:02:31,985
That hurts! You smacked too hard!

39
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:33,236
Sakura-san!

40
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:35,196
You know each other?

41
00:02:37,198 --> 00:02:39,367
Yeah, from my first day in town.

42
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:42,954
You were so pumped up
before the session even started!

43
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:44,998
I knew you would become the grade captain!

44
00:02:45,081 --> 00:02:47,041
Don't start spoutin' random stuff, man.

45
00:02:50,545 --> 00:02:52,130
Huh? Come again?

46
00:02:52,213 --> 00:02:53,590
Sakura-san!

47
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:56,676
I heard you won against Togame too, huh?

48
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,720
Yeah...

49
00:02:58,803 --> 00:03:00,054
I can hear him now.

50
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:02,599
The second-year captains
are the same as last year.

51
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:08,313
Oh, you don't have to do that.

52
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:13,401
So Sakura's the grade captain
for the first years?

53
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:17,822
I'm counting on you guys too, Nirei, Suo!

54
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:20,450
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir!

55
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:25,121
But if you run into any problems,
just rely on your seniors.

56
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:28,541
We're like your big brothers.
We've got your back!

57
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:33,087
You guys help them too, okay, Kaji?

58
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:36,758
Tell them things you wished
you knew in your first year!

59
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:38,051
Yes, sir.

60
00:03:41,512 --> 00:03:42,555
What?

61
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:47,310
For the most part,
you deal with things on your own.

62
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:49,145
There isn't much I can do.

63
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:52,357
Plus, I'm not your big brother
or anything.

64
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,650
I'm a single child.

65
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:57,195
Yeah, I know that much.

66
00:03:57,278 --> 00:03:59,739
That's not really what you meant, right?

67
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:03,034
Don't you have some better advice, s<i>enpai?</i>

68
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:13,878
Oh, they're back!

69
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:16,172
So what was it about?

70
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:18,675
It was a meet-up event
for the grade captains!

71
00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:20,343
I'm so touched!

72
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:22,679
What? So the Four Kings were there, too?

73
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:23,972
Yeah, they were.

74
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:25,807
For real?

75
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:27,016
How nice.

76
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:31,187
I'd love to hear about
the Four Kings' virtues.

77
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,773
Yes! Makes you curious, right?

78
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:52,625
Hey, since we're not patrolling today,
how 'bout we drop by Muscle Power?

79
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:54,377
Oh, yeah! Let's do it!

80
00:04:55,336 --> 00:04:56,838
I'll pass.

81
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:02,593
Nope, he's not here.

82
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,514
It'll be a pain if we go
too deep into the town.

83
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:08,016
I know.

84
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:10,310
You guys looking for something?

85
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:12,854
If you are, we'll help.

86
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:19,652
Oh, yeah. Great timing.

87
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:22,780
We were just looking for you people.

88
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:24,365
But...

89
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:28,536
it looks like you guys are not it.

90
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:32,665
Bye.

91
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:38,004
That symbol... Is that...

92
00:05:38,379 --> 00:05:39,422
Yeah.

93
00:05:39,505 --> 00:05:42,091
Blue dragon skeleton on a white jacket.

94
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:43,092
It's KEEL.

95
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:45,887
KEEL? The heck are they?

96
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:47,555
I don't know the details myself,

97
00:05:48,139 --> 00:05:50,391
but they're not a very big group.

98
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:54,520
However, just like the ones we just met,
there aren't any good rumors about them.

99
00:05:54,604 --> 00:05:57,523
And those guys were lookin' for us?

100
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:59,400
But I don't know those people.

101
00:05:59,484 --> 00:06:03,613
From the way he phrased it,
they were looking for someone in Furin.

102
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,785
Hey, are you okay?

103
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:11,954
Dear! Dear! Come, quick!

104
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:19,504
Anzai-san?

105
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:34,894
You... Hey, you!

106
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:40,399
Thank goodness! Are you awake?

107
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:43,236
Are you okay, Anzai-san?

108
00:06:44,153 --> 00:06:46,781
For now, come to our place and rest.

109
00:06:46,864 --> 00:06:49,200
Yeah...

110
00:06:50,284 --> 00:06:52,370
Well, about that...

111
00:06:52,453 --> 00:06:54,705
I was chased by a dog!

112
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:56,249
Huh?

113
00:06:56,332 --> 00:06:59,252
A bear-like large dog about
this size was chasing me,

114
00:06:59,335 --> 00:07:01,587
so I was hiding over there.

115
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:04,090
But then I got so relieved, I fell asleep.

116
00:07:04,173 --> 00:07:07,844
Anzai-kun, where do I have
to go to meet that bear?

117
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:09,595
I'd love to spar with it!

118
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,639
Tsuge-chan, it wasn't a literal bear.

119
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:12,807
Hey, you.

120
00:07:13,599 --> 00:07:16,477
If you're gonna lie, tell a better one.

121
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:19,897
Yeah, it was so obviously a lie,
even Sakura-san could tell.

122
00:07:19,981 --> 00:07:22,150
Yeah, that Sakura-kun who's so gullible.

123
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:24,235
Okay, let's take this outside, you punks!

124
00:07:24,318 --> 00:07:27,029
No really! It's nothing!

125
00:07:27,113 --> 00:07:29,949
I got something to do after this,
so I should get going now.

126
00:07:30,032 --> 00:07:32,577
Thanks, ma'am! I'll come
by next time for your monja!

127
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:34,871
Huh? You're leaving already?

128
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,914
You should rest a little more.

129
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:38,541
I'm fine, really.

130
00:07:38,624 --> 00:07:40,376
There we go.

131
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:41,794
Anzai-kun.

132
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:44,130
Did something happen between you and KEEL?

133
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:53,139
What are you talking about?

134
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:55,391
<i>He's so easy to read.</i>

135
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:57,810
Oh, are you talking about beer?

136
00:07:57,894 --> 00:08:00,354
Come on, guys. No alcohol
until you're over 20!

137
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:03,065
See ya, ma'am! I'm going now!

138
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:04,484
See you guys at school!

139
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:06,652
If you're leaving, take this...

140
00:08:09,113 --> 00:08:12,492
I was hoping to give him
some freshly made ones...

141
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:16,078
We're always getting help
and protected by the Furin kids.

142
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:18,414
We can't thank you kids enough.

143
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:21,000
Go ahead and order
anything you want, kids!

144
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:22,043
Yay!

145
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:23,377
For real, ma'am?

146
00:08:23,461 --> 00:08:25,087
I'll have a cheese mochi mentai!

147
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:27,173
But we haven't done anything.
Are you sure?

148
00:08:27,256 --> 00:08:28,966
Why, of course!

149
00:08:29,383 --> 00:08:33,596
You Furin kids are like my own sons!

150
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:36,807
Hey, Suo.

151
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:40,311
How did you know Anzai-kun
was involved with KEEL?

152
00:08:40,394 --> 00:08:43,272
It wasn't like I was completely sure.

153
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:47,944
But judging from the KEEL guy's wording
and Anzai-kun's state,

154
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:50,446
I simply thought there
might be a connection.

155
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:53,991
But well, I suppose I was right.

156
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:56,160
Sakura-san!

157
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:57,662
What should we do?

158
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:00,414
If Suo-san's prediction was right,

159
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:03,251
that means Anzai-kun got
those bruises from KEEL!

160
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:05,211
That means we must save him!

161
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:07,755
Sakura-san! A classmate is in trouble!

162
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:09,298
Wait, hold on a sec!

163
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:13,678
Even if he did get involved with KEEL,
he didn't say a thing to us.

164
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:17,181
That means he's got his own plans.

165
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:21,852
Besides, we don't even know
for sure if he <i>wants</i> our help.

166
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:23,688
But...

167
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:25,231
Anyone...

168
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:28,985
has one or two things
they don't want to talk about.

169
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:37,410
Even so, he's still our friend
from the same class.

170
00:09:37,952 --> 00:09:41,872
If there's something we can do,
don't you want to lend him a hand?

171
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:45,167
<i>I want you guys to watch
and help all of our friends.</i>

172
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:51,007
I'm leaving.

173
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:54,594
What? Wait, Sakura-san!
We're not done talking...

174
00:09:54,677 --> 00:09:56,971
Oh, you're leaving too?

175
00:09:57,054 --> 00:09:58,973
Then take this with you.

176
00:10:03,769 --> 00:10:07,690
Sakura-chan can be bashful at times.

177
00:10:07,815 --> 00:10:11,027
Down to his core... and every part of him.

178
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:14,697
But the monja's so good.

179
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:18,326
Nirei-kun, it'll be okay.

180
00:10:20,369 --> 00:10:22,371
Hey, are you all right?

181
00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:24,540
Are those injuries their doing too?

182
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:27,752
This is nothing!

183
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,254
What about Nagato?

184
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:34,050
I failed.

185
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:36,636
I couldn't bring him with me.

186
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:41,015
That group is seriously dangerous.

187
00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:46,395
At this rate, Nagato's going to cross
a line he can't come back from.

188
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:52,151
Say, how about we talk
about this with the guys at Furin...

189
00:10:52,234 --> 00:10:53,653
We can't do that!

190
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:55,905
Sorry.

191
00:10:56,572 --> 00:10:58,240
But we can't do that.

192
00:10:58,324 --> 00:10:59,408
TONPU MARKET STREET

193
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,744
<i>Furin... The Bofurin...</i>

194
00:11:02,953 --> 00:11:05,373
<i>They're the group that protects the town.</i>

195
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:08,834
This is my personal problem.

196
00:11:09,335 --> 00:11:11,003
I won't drag the others into it.

197
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:12,004
What?

198
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:15,174
Then I'll go with you next time!

199
00:11:15,257 --> 00:11:18,094
Don't be stupid! It's too dangerous!

200
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:29,021
Don't worry! Just leave it to me!

201
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:33,484
I can do it on my own!

202
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:44,537
How can he say it's okay
with a face like that?

203
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:47,706
With all those injuries...

204
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:51,252
What's "okay" about any of this?

205
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:53,546
Hey.

206
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:58,134
Tell me more... about what
you guys were talking about.

207
00:12:03,013 --> 00:12:05,599
Who... are you?

208
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:08,811
I'm from the same class
as that guy just now.

209
00:12:08,894 --> 00:12:11,105
Tell me more about this thing.

210
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:15,526
FURIN

211
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:24,452
Anzai and I have been friends
since we were little.

212
00:12:24,535 --> 00:12:28,080
And we used to play together often
in this park ever since then.

213
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:32,960
<i>And in between,
a boy named Nagato joined us.</i>

214
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:37,756
<i>Anzai and I were pretty naughty.
We did reckless stuff and got hurt often.</i>

215
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,885
<i>Nagato was a very quiet and kind boy,</i>

216
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:44,013
<i>but he still went along
with all our crazy ideas.</i>

217
00:12:44,847 --> 00:12:48,058
<i>We all went to different high schools,</i>

218
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:51,645
<i>but I thought we'd remain best friends.</i>

219
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:53,397
<i>But...</i>

220
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,692
Oh, Anzai, it's you!

221
00:12:56,775 --> 00:12:58,444
Long time no see!

222
00:12:58,527 --> 00:13:02,072
Though it hasn't actually been
that long since graduation.

223
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:06,243
Oh, that face...
You got into a fight again, didn't you?

224
00:13:06,327 --> 00:13:07,953
You never change.

225
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:12,082
Nagato's gonna be mad again.
He'll be like, "You had a fight again?"

226
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,668
Now I kinda want to see Nagato, too.

227
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:20,925
I got these injuries from
a group named KEEL...

228
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:22,218
KEEL?

229
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:26,847
Today I saw one of them
try to steal a bag,

230
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:28,641
so I tried to catch them.

231
00:13:28,724 --> 00:13:33,062
It was outside the town,
but I couldn't just leave it be.

232
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:35,814
I grabbed his arm...

233
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:38,484
and took off the hood covering his face...

234
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:40,152
Then...

235
00:13:40,861 --> 00:13:42,530
Who do you think it was?

236
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:50,037
It was... Nagato.

237
00:13:50,829 --> 00:13:54,124
Nagato was not the type of guy
who would do that!

238
00:13:54,208 --> 00:14:00,256
That's why today Anzai was supposed
to bring Nagato here so we could talk,

239
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:04,510
but he came back alone...
completely beat up.

240
00:14:05,219 --> 00:14:08,347
<i>When I asked him,
he wouldn't tell me the details.</i>

241
00:14:08,430 --> 00:14:11,642
<i>He said it's dangerous,
but he's trying to solve this on his own,</i>

242
00:14:11,725 --> 00:14:16,230
saying that it's his personal problem,
so he can't get Furin involved.

243
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:19,567
<i>So that's why he didn't say anything?</i>

244
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:25,739
Why are you crying?

245
00:14:26,907 --> 00:14:31,287
My childhood friends are suffering,
but I can't do anything.

246
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:35,624
All I can do is look on.
It's so frustrating.

247
00:14:37,001 --> 00:14:40,004
It's frustrating that I'm so powerless.

248
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,010
Fine...

249
00:14:46,510 --> 00:14:50,264
I just have to drag that
Nagato guy here, right?

250
00:14:50,347 --> 00:14:51,432
Huh?

251
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:56,896
But Anzai said Furin's job is to protect
the town, so he couldn't involve you guys.

252
00:14:56,979 --> 00:14:59,773
Well, you know, it's that.
Things will work out.

253
00:14:59,857 --> 00:15:01,734
We're in the same class, after all.

254
00:15:01,817 --> 00:15:03,736
And I'm a lot stronger than you.

255
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:08,115
You can just say, "Just leave it to us."

256
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:10,618
So...

257
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:14,955
Just leave it to me.

258
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:22,087
You're a nice guy.

259
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:25,424
Thank you.

260
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:30,763
It's not like that!
You were crying, so I had to!

261
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:34,516
Then I really do have to thank you.

262
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:39,229
Now that I feel kind of relieved,
I feel like I'm starving.

263
00:15:39,313 --> 00:15:41,440
Huh? I ain't giving you any.

264
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:42,441
Huh?

265
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:44,985
Yeah. I'm not asking for it.

266
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,992
<i>That being said...</i>

267
00:15:52,534 --> 00:15:54,620
<i>how should I handle this?</i>

268
00:15:55,955 --> 00:15:58,207
-Good morning, Sakura-kun!
-Mornin'!

269
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:00,501
-Morning.
-Good morning!

270
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:03,253
No, for real!

271
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:06,966
I tangled with a bear and
it took everything I had to escape!

272
00:16:07,049 --> 00:16:10,010
Don't lie to us. Come on, who hit you?

273
00:16:10,094 --> 00:16:11,971
We promise we won't laugh. Just tell us.

274
00:16:12,805 --> 00:16:17,017
<i>I bet he'll just deflect the topic
no matter what I say to him.</i>

275
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:23,482
Sakura-kun, did you talk
with Anzai-kun yesterday?

276
00:16:23,607 --> 00:16:26,402
Huh? What are you talking about?

277
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:29,405
You're an open book, Sakura-chan.

278
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:32,616
Hey, is Anzai here?

279
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:35,119
I'm here! What's up?

280
00:16:35,202 --> 00:16:36,662
Oh, hey.

281
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:37,663
Who's that?

282
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:40,374
He's Tochimoto-san from class four.

283
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:43,669
What's this? A love letter?

284
00:16:43,752 --> 00:16:46,672
Who on earth puts a love letter
inside a brown envelope?

285
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:50,592
When I was on my way to school,
a guy asked me to hand you this.

286
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:54,680
He had a hood on, you know.
Looked really creepy.

287
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:10,195
Anzai-san?

288
00:17:11,113 --> 00:17:12,156
Sakura-san?

289
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:16,326
Hey, wait!

290
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:17,995
I said, wait!

291
00:17:25,794 --> 00:17:27,046
You little...

292
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:29,089
Hold up!

293
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:33,010
What's your problem? Move out of the way!

294
00:17:33,093 --> 00:17:36,805
I heard what happened from the girl
you were at the park with yesterday.

295
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:39,058
Huh? Why would Tsuchiya tell you?

296
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:41,060
That doesn't matter right now.

297
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:42,770
That came from KEEL, right?

298
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:46,690
Hey! Wai...

299
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:52,071
What a bunch of scum.

300
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:53,947
NAGATO-KUN IS BEATEN UP
SEE YOU AT SENKAN SHIPYARD!!

301
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:56,283
This is none of your goddamn business!

302
00:17:59,244 --> 00:18:00,704
What now?

303
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:05,459
Tell me everything, Anzai.

304
00:18:10,297 --> 00:18:11,924
It was two days ago.

305
00:18:18,263 --> 00:18:20,766
<i>I encountered a guy
who was stealing a bag.</i>

306
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:25,229
<i>So I grabbed him and took off his hood.</i>

307
00:18:27,147 --> 00:18:28,273
<i>But he was...</i>

308
00:18:29,024 --> 00:18:31,860
<i>my childhood friend, Nagato.</i>

309
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:38,700
He punched me and ran away,
leaving the bag he stole.

310
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:43,122
That's why I went back there yesterday.

311
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:46,917
To check what happened to him.

312
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:55,676
Hey now, this isn't enough, you know?

313
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:59,680
Didn't you give me the same excuse before?

314
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:01,598
I'm sorry.

315
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:05,686
Man, what a pickle we're in, eh?
But if you aren't got enough, so be it.

316
00:19:05,769 --> 00:19:08,480
Let's do that again, shall we?

317
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:10,315
One punch for 1,000 yen.

318
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:14,236
With ten punches,
I'll say you brought back 10,000 yen.

319
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:16,029
Let's start.

320
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:17,781
1,000 yen.

321
00:19:17,865 --> 00:19:19,491
2,000 yen.

322
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:21,368
3,000 yen.

323
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:30,419
Whoa, what's this?

324
00:19:35,090 --> 00:19:37,259
Let's go, Nagato! Hurry!

325
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:45,893
What are you... doing?

326
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:47,728
What do you mean?

327
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:53,901
This has nothing to do with you.

328
00:19:56,862 --> 00:20:00,782
I have decided... to stay here.

329
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:09,499
Don't stick your neck
where it doesn't belong!

330
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:18,550
After that, I somehow managed to run
back to the shopping district.

331
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,302
And the rest you know.

332
00:20:20,427 --> 00:20:24,014
After all the crap they did to him,
he still decided to stay?

333
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:26,099
Why's that?

334
00:20:26,183 --> 00:20:27,684
I don't know.

335
00:20:27,768 --> 00:20:29,186
But...

336
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:30,270
he...

337
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:32,356
<i>was crying!</i>

338
00:20:32,898 --> 00:20:35,108
When he broke his leg
when we were playing,

339
00:20:35,192 --> 00:20:37,694
when we got lost and felt
we wouldn't make it home,

340
00:20:37,778 --> 00:20:40,572
Nagato was kind and quiet...

341
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:42,824
But he was strong!

342
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:44,868
I don't know what happened to him,

343
00:20:45,452 --> 00:20:47,621
<i>but he was crying.</i>

344
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:50,457
<i>That's all the reason I need.</i>

345
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:53,085
<i>I will...</i>

346
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:57,256
get him out of there!

347
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:00,342
I see.

348
00:21:01,176 --> 00:21:02,094
Let's go.

349
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:06,056
Why are you coming with me?

350
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:08,141
This is my personal problem!

351
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:11,645
Plus, KEEL's really
a group of dangerous thugs!

352
00:21:11,728 --> 00:21:15,023
I can't involve you...
involve Furin in this...

353
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:16,608
What are you saying?

354
00:21:17,359 --> 00:21:19,945
It doesn't matter who I'm up against.

355
00:21:20,028 --> 00:21:22,781
And I'm not planning to go
as a member of Furin.

356
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:26,368
<i>I promised that girl.</i>

357
00:21:27,244 --> 00:21:29,997
<i>that I will drag that
Nagato guy out of there.</i>

358
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:32,124
Involving me, you say?

359
00:21:32,207 --> 00:21:35,252
Stop talkin' like
you're the center of the universe.

360
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:38,839
This is my problem.

361
00:21:40,549 --> 00:21:43,635
I see. So that's what's going on.

362
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:55,063
You guys... Why?

363
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:58,608
{\an8}You did this yesterday,
and just earlier as well.

364
00:21:58,692 --> 00:22:01,445
{\an8}If you wanna hide it,
you should do a better job of it.

365
00:22:01,528 --> 00:22:03,613
{\an8}Aren't we pals, man?

366
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:05,574
{\an8}Why you didn't tell us anything?

367
00:22:06,283 --> 00:22:08,243
But... I mean...

368
00:22:09,036 --> 00:22:11,997
Furin's job is to protect the town, right?

369
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:16,001
It's not like we're all here
because we're Furin.

370
00:22:16,084 --> 00:22:20,672
{\an8}Not saving people in need
goes against my virtue, that's all.

371
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:23,633
{\an8}Yes! I'm going because I want to help!

372
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:26,845
{\an8}It's just like what they're saying.

373
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:29,306
{\an8}We just want to save our pal.

374
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:36,938
You guys...

375
00:22:37,606 --> 00:22:41,151
Come on, we'll leave you behind
if you don't hurry.

376
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:45,072
Sorry I had to wake you up
from your sleep,

377
00:22:45,155 --> 00:22:49,034
but if you're the only one behind
when the whole class runs off to help...

378
00:22:49,117 --> 00:22:52,537
I imagine Umemiya-san is going to be sad.

379
00:22:52,621 --> 00:22:55,624
So Sugishita-kun said
he'll be coming, too!

380
00:23:02,380 --> 00:23:03,423
{\an8}What?

381
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:07,636
Huh? What are those guys doing?

382
00:23:09,805 --> 00:23:11,473
Where are we going again?

383
00:23:11,556 --> 00:23:14,434
The abandoned Senkan shipyard, apparently.

384
00:23:14,518 --> 00:23:17,187
That must be KEEL's base.

385
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:22,359
{\an8}Based on the picture, it doesn't look like
we've got that much time to spare.

386
00:23:22,442 --> 00:23:23,902
I know.

387
00:23:33,537 --> 00:23:34,621
Hey.

388
00:23:34,704 --> 00:23:36,957
No matter what you say, I'm going!

389
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,708
I'm also part of the group!

390
00:23:40,669 --> 00:23:42,212
Make sure you keep up.

391
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:44,631
Yes!

